}}

On February 10, 2024, the [[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] (ATAS, also known as the Television Academy) announced that the 76th Primetime Emmy Awards would be held on September 15; the corresponding Creative Arts ceremonies were announced for September 7 and 8.<ref>{{cite news |last=Porter |first=Rick |title=Emmy Awards Return to September Berth on ABC |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/2024-emmy-awards-date-abc-1235821555/ |access-date=September 14, 2024 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=February 10, 2024 |archive-date=September 29, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240929075918/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/2024-emmy-awards-date-abc-1235821555/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schneider |first=Michael |title=Emmys Move Back to Sunday, as ABC Reveals 2024 Ceremony Date |url=https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/emmys-2024-ceremony-date-sunday-abc-1235906681/ |access-date=September 14, 2024 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=February 10, 2024 |archive-date=September 28, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240928092607/https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/emmys-2024-ceremony-date-sunday-abc-1235906681/ |url-status=live}}</ref> It was the second Primetime Emmy Awards ceremony held in 2024 due to the [[75th Primetime Emmy Awards|75th ceremony]], originally slated to broadcast on September 18, 2023, taking place four months later on January 15, 2024, as a result of the [[2023 Hollywood labor disputes]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Seitz |first=Loree |title=2024 Emmys Set September Date for 76th Awards Ceremony |url=https://www.thewrap.com/emmy-awards-2024-date-announcement/ |access-date=September 15, 2024 |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=February 10, 2024 |archive-date=September 15, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915072908/https://www.thewrap.com/emmy-awards-2024-date-announcement/ |url-status=live}}</ref> [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] broadcast the gala as part of a four-year rotation deal among the "[[Big Three (American television)|Big Four]]" broadcast networks signed in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-renews-big-four-deal-8-years-1132446/ |title=Emmys Renew Big Four Deal for 8 Years |last=O'Connell |first=Mikey |date=August 6, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=December 7, 2021 |archive-date=December 7, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207184542/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-renews-big-four-deal-8-years-1132446/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The broadcast was made available for streaming on [[Hulu]] for the week following the ceremony.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/how-to-watch-the-emmys-1235137539/ |title=76th Annual Emmys: How to Watch Live on TV & Stream Online |last=Muhammad |first=Latifah |date=September 15, 2024 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-date=September 25, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240925121434/https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/how-to-watch-the-emmys-1235137539/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

The ceremony was produced by Jesse Collins Entertainment (Jesse Collins, Dionne Harmon, and Jeannae Rouzan-Clay) for the second consecutive year.<ref>{{cite news |last=White |first=Peter |title=Jesse Collins Entertainment to Produce Emmys, Again |url=https://deadline.com/2024/07/jesse-collins-entertainment-emmys-1236010506/ |access-date=September 14, 2024 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 15, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915064857/https://deadline.com/2024/07/jesse-collins-entertainment-emmys-1236010506/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Actor [[Eugene Levy]] and his son [[Dan Levy (Canadian actor)|Dan]] were announced as co-hosts on August 16.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schneider |first=Michael |title=Eugene and Dan Levy Officially Set as Emmys Hosts |url=https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/eugene-dan-levy-emmys-host-sept-15-1236108670/ |access-date=September 15, 2024 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=August 16, 2024 |archive-date=September 10, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240910053153/https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/eugene-dan-levy-emmys-host-sept-15-1236108670/ |url-status=live}}</ref> It was the first time a father-and-son duo co-hosted an Emmy ceremony.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kennedy |first=Mark |title=Eugene Levy and Dan Levy will make history as the first father-and-son co-hosts of the Emmys |url=https://apnews.com/article/dany-eugene-levy-emmys-hosts-2024-e449e02df26b9df39f5b4d23680c5b36 |access-date=September 15, 2024 |publisher=[[Associated Press]] |date=August 16, 2024 |archive-date=September 15, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915043616/https://apnews.com/article/dany-eugene-levy-emmys-hosts-2024-e449e02df26b9df39f5b4d23680c5b36 |url-status=live}}</ref> According to [[Disney Entertainment]] chairperson [[Dana Walden]], producers and network executives had asked comedian [[Jimmy Kimmel]] – who emceed the previous three ABC telecasts – to host the ceremony. However, Kimmel declined the offer saying he wanted to take a break after hosting the [[96th Academy Awards|previous Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Connell |first=Mikey |title=Dana Walden on Disney's Emmy Noms, ''Shogun'' Futurem and Giving Kimmel a Hosting Break |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/emmy-nominations-2024-dana-walden-shogun-the-bear-1235951434/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 17, 2024 |archive-date=September 25, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240925152509/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/emmy-nominations-2024-dana-walden-shogun-the-bear-1235951434/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Alex Rudzinski and [[Rickey Minor]] served as director and musical director for the ceremony, respectively.<ref>{{cite news |last=Petski |first=Denise |title=Emmy Awards Sets Full Production Team |url=https://deadline.com/2024/08/emmy-awards-full-production-team-1236041864/ |access-date=September 10, 2024 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 20, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240920184041/https://deadline.com/2024/08/emmy-awards-full-production-team-1236041864/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Two days before the ceremony, ABC aired a special episode of ''[[20/20 (American TV program)|20/20]]'' entitled ''The 76th Emmys: A Night of Firsts''. Hosted by ''[[Good Morning America]]'' co-anchor [[Robin Roberts (newscaster)|Robin Roberts]], the special featured interviews with Eugene and Dan Levy and several of the ceremony's nominees.<ref>{{cite news |last=Petsky |first=Denise |title=Robin Roberts to Host Emmy Primetime Special & Red Carpet Live Pre-Show with Will Reeve |url=https://deadline.com/2024/09/robin-roberts-host-emmy-primetime-red-carpet-special-abc-1236082665/ |access-date=September 22, 2024 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=September 9, 2024 |archive-date=September 22, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240922074340/https://deadline.com/2024/09/robin-roberts-host-emmy-primetime-red-carpet-special-abc-1236082665/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Roberts also co-hosted the network's red carpet arrivals special preceding the main telecast with [[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]] journalist Will Reeve.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dunaj |first=Mikhayla |title=How to Watch the 2024 Emmy Awards for Free on ABC |url=https://www.mlive.com/tv/2024/09/how-to-watch-the-2024-emmy-awards-for-free-on-abc.html |access-date=September 22, 2024 |publisher=[[MLive Media Group]] |date=September 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 22, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240922074827/https://www.mlive.com/tv/2024/09/how-to-watch-the-2024-emmy-awards-for-free-on-abc.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Building from the previous year, producers Collins, Harmon, and Rouzan-Clay announced during a press conference that several of the awards would be presented by actors grouped by "character archetypes", such as TV moms, dads, and villains.<ref name="The Wrap Emmy Preview">{{cite news |last=Seitz |first=Loree |title=Emmys EPs Tease Tributes for ''SNL 50th'', ''Happy Days'', and 'Characters You've Loved Over the Years' |url=https://www.thewrap.com/emmys-2024-snl-happy-days-tribute-preview-jesse-collins/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=September 12, 2024 |archive-date=September 16, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916012405/https://www.thewrap.com/emmys-2024-snl-happy-days-tribute-preview-jesse-collins/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Collins also revealed that the telecast would feature reunions in tribute to the 50th anniversaries of [[NBC]] variety/sketch program ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' and ABC comedy series ''[[Happy Days]]'', and the 25th anniversary of NBC drama series ''[[The West Wing]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Connell |first=Mikey |title=Emmys Preview: Producers Talk ''SNL'' Reunion, Levy Chemistry, and Leaning Deeper into Nostalgia |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-preview-cast-reunions-saturday-night-live-happy-days-surprise-1235999780/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 12, 2024 |archive-date=September 21, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240921152134/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-preview-cast-reunions-saturday-night-live-happy-days-surprise-1235999780/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In an interview with the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', Eugene Levy echoed the producers' decision to focus on history and nostalgia, saying, "And [it's] also just paying tribute to television, certainly the nominees, but to the medium that gave us both our starts."<ref>{{cite news |last=Lloyd |first=Robert |title=As Emmy Hosts, Eugene and Dan Levy want to Make the Show a 'Light and Bright' Night |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2024-09-15/emmys-review-2024-dan-eugene-levy |access-date=September 19, 2024 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=September 11, 2024 |archive-date=September 29, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240929080030/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2024-09-15/emmys-review-2024-dan-eugene-levy |url-status=live}}</ref>

Categories to be shown during the main broadcast were set in July 2024, with [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Special (Live)|Outstanding Variety Special (Live)]] returning to the Creative Arts ceremony; as part of a rotation agreement with the [[Writers Guild of America]], [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Special|Outstanding Writing for a Variety Special]] also replaced [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series|Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series]] at the main ceremony.<ref>{{cite news |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |title=Emmys 2024: Category Breakdown by Night Revealed |url=https://deadline.com/2024/07/emmys-2024-category-breakdown-1236021736/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 25, 2024 |archive-date=July 26, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240726225425/https://deadline.com/2024/07/emmys-2024-category-breakdown-1236021736/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Critical reviews and viewership===
The broadcast generally received mixed to negative reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web |title=Emmys: 76th Emmys |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/emmys/s76/reviews |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240924080459/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/emmys/s76/reviews |url-status=live}}</ref> Allison Herman of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' compared the ceremony to the previous one noting, "the 76th Emmys were a far less dynamic and more stilted watch than the January show." She also criticized production elements such as the music director's choices for presenters' walk on music, recurring sound technical issues, and the grouping of presenters based on character archetypes.<ref>{{cite news |last=Herman |first=Allison |title=A Humdrum Emmys Are Weighed Down by Sparse Crowds and Sponsored Content: TV Review |url=https://variety.com/2024/tv/tv-reviews/emmys-2024-review-eugene-dan-levy-1236145523/ |access-date=September 24, 2024 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=September 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240924123117/https://variety.com/2024/tv/tv-reviews/emmys-2024-review-eugene-dan-levy-1236145523/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Ben Travers of ''[[IndieWire]]'' found Eugene and Dan Levy's performances as hosts underwhelming, which was not helped by their reminder to the audience that "they weren't stand up comedians, but actors acting like hosts." He reserved praise for several presenters such as [[Candice Bergen]], [[Billy Crystal]], and the cast of ''[[Only Murders in the Building]]'', but he ultimately found the ceremony to be "another awards show resigned to its diminishing fate."<ref>{{cite news |last=Travers |first=Ben |title=The Emmys Could've Been an Email |url=https://www.indiewire.com/criticism/shows/emmys-review-2024-1235047972/ |access-date=September 27, 2024 |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=September 15, 2024}}</ref> Lili Loofbourow, writing for ''[[The Washington Post]]'', found the hosts to be "pleasant but forgettable" and that the onslaught of repeat winners bogged down the ceremony.<ref>{{cite news |last=Loofbourow |first=Lila |title=Last Night's Emmy Awards Felt Like a Rerun |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/2024/09/16/emmy-awards-2024-review/ |access-date=September 27, 2024 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 16, 2024 |archive-date=September 16, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916221057/https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/2024/09/16/emmy-awards-2024-review/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

In a more positive review, Judy Berman of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' complimented the Levys and said, "The emcees imbued what is always a long night—and was, this time around, full of predictable wins—with many moments of lighthearted fun, without trying too hard to roast their fellow actors or land headline-making zingers."<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Berman |first=Judy |title=Eugene and Dan Levy Made Hosting the Emmys Look Easy |url=https://time.com/7021458/emmys-2024-review-eugene-dan-levy/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=September 16, 2024 |archive-date=September 19, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240919034713/https://time.com/7021458/emmys-2024-review-eugene-dan-levy/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Daniel Fienberg of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' called the ceremony "an above-average show", noting that surprise winners kept "audiences on their toes" and that they often gave the best speeches. However, he criticized the reunion tributes noting that the presenters' dialogue felt bland and poor written in comparison to the prior ceremony's tributes. He also called the choice of [[Jelly Roll (singer)|Jelly Roll]]'s performance of "[[I Am Not Okay]]" "tonally questionable" and wrote that [[Jimmy Kimmel]]'s tribute to comedian [[Bob Newhart]] "absolutely warped the mood in a room that wasn't sure if this was the time to laugh about how often [[Jon Stewart]] wins Emmys."<ref>{{cite news |last=Fienberg |first=Daniel |title=Critic's Notebook: 76th Primetime Emmy Awards Oscillate Between Freshness and Fatigue |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-reviews/2024-emmys-critics-analysis-review-1236003442/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240924123117/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-reviews/2024-emmys-critics-analysis-review-1236003442/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Robert Lloyd wrote in the ''Los Angeles Times'' that the telecast was a "sweet, positive show that at the same time avoided the air of self-congratulation". He noted the Levys' "father-and-son dynamic", with Dan's role as "the hipper son" and Eugene as the "befuddled dad", was at the heart of their shared time together.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lloyd |first=Robert |title=Review: Eugene and Dan Levy Hosted Positive Emmys Show Themed Around Age |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2024-09-15/emmys-review-2024-dan-eugene-levy |access-date=September 19, 2024 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=September 15, 2024 |archive-date=September 18, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918183214/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2024-09-15/emmys-review-2024-dan-eugene-levy |url-status=live}}</ref>

Competing with a ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football|Sunday Night Football]]'' game on NBC, the ceremony was viewed by 6.9&nbsp;million people in the United States, making it the most-viewed Emmys in [[73rd Primetime Emmy Awards|three years]], representing a 54% increase over the previous year's ceremony.<ref name="Ratings">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-2024-tv-ratings-1236004078/ |title=TV Ratings: Emmys Jump by 55 Percent, Stop Streak of All-Time Lows |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |first=Rick |last=Porter |date=September 16, 2024 |access-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-date=September 25, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240925120413/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/emmys-2024-tv-ratings-1236004078/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Emmys Audience on ABC Nears 6.9 Million, Highest in Three Years |url=https://www.reuters.com/business/media-telecom/emmys-audience-abc-nears-69-million-highest-three-years-2024-09-16/ |access-date=September 19, 2024 |publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=September 17, 2024 |archive-date=September 24, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240924203941/https://www.reuters.com/business/media-telecom/emmys-audience-abc-nears-69-million-highest-three-years-2024-09-16/ |url-status=live}}</ref> It also achieved a 1.03 rating among adults ages 18–49.<ref name="Ratings"/>

==In Memoriam==
